Pseudocode for gcd, gcd_3, is_prime, and get_factors

Pseudocode for gcd

gcd function takes input a, b  
  if a or b are not positive  
    stop function and output error message  
  if a or b are not integers  
    stop function and output error message  
    
  between a and b, assign the larger one to variable bigger and smaller one to variable smaller  
    
  set variable remainder to be the remainder of bigger / smaller  
  while the remainder is not 0  
    assign remainder to temp  
    assign smaller to remainder  
    assign smaller to temp  
   
 return smaller

Pseudocode for gcd_3

gcd_3 function takes input a, b, c  
  if a or b or c are not positive  
    stop function and output error message  
  if a or b or care not integers  
    stop function and output error message  
   
 run gcd function on a and b, and assign the result to gcd_ab  
 run gcd function on gcd_ab and c

Pseudocode for is_prime

is_prime function takes input x  
  for each value in x  
    if value is less than or equal to 0  
      stop function and output error message  
    if value is not an integer  
      stop function and output error message  
    
  initialize prime_bool  
  for each value_1 in x  
    if value_1 is 1  
      assign FALSE to a temp variable  
    if value_1 is 2  
      assign TRUE to the temp variable  
    else  
      assign TRUE to the temp variable  
      for each value_2 from 2 to the square root of value_1 rounded up  
        if value_1 is divisible by value_2  
          assign FALSE to the temp variable and break  
    attach the temp variable to prime_bool  
  return prime_bool

Pseudocode for get_factors

get_factors function takes input x  
  if x is not positive  
    stop function and output error message  
  if x is not an integer  
    stop function and output error message  
    
  assign x to temp_x  
  initialize prime_factors  
  loop value from 2 to temp_x  
    while temp_x is still visible by the value  
      if the value is prime  
        add it to prime_factors  
        reassign temp_x to be itself divided by the value  
      else  
        next  
  return prime_factors
